dct_alternative_sm: The border areas of Austria-Hungary and Serbia
dct_description_sm: Druck and Verlag der Kartogr. Anstalt G. Freytag & Berndt, Ges. m. b. H., Wien.
Relief shown by shading, spot heights.
Boundaries distinguished by coloring, with countries under rule of Austria-Hungary in yellow.
Shows roads, railroads (including under construction), forts, waterways, passes.

Territories are those before the end of World War 1, with Albania and Montenegro as indepedent states and Romania occupying Old Romania borders, dating this map between 1912 (when Albania becomes independent) and 1915 (before Montenegro is occupied by Austria-Hungary in 1916).
